summary: as TJ is typically back every 2 episodes , do you think there's a certain reason why he'll be absent for 4 episodes between...
question: as TJ is typically back every 2 episodes , do you think there's a certain reason why he'll be absent for 4 episodes between episode 15 and 19 like do you think something might happen to make him I guess back away??
answer:
I think those episodes are going to have to have a heavier focus on the Mack family, because they are the episodes surrounding Bex and Bowie’s wedding. Of course his absence from those episodes will benefit the decision to not have TJ attend the wedding with Cyrus as well, because he will be out of sight/out of mind.

But I wouldn’t say he’s “typically” back every 2 episodes anyways. In fact, a three episode absence is pretty common for TJ’s character. We have seen in happen multiple times (episodes 214/15/16, 218/19/20, 222/23/24, 301/02/03, and again with 316/17/18). Those gaps in season 2 are very good to compare this to, because usually when he was absent - it was to make room to focus something else, like Buffy’s moving storyline. It was important for that storyline to have episodes focus on the relationship of the GHC, just like they’re gonna have to focus on Andi’s family more leading up to the wedding. And those periods of absence lead up to something big, the look back, so I definitely don’t TJ not being at the wedding will damage our chances of endgame. 

I don’t think they’ll need to provide an in-universe reasoning for his absence, as they never have before, but they could I guess. He just won’t be involved in the stories for those eps.

title: In the texts between Andi and Amber
body:
Amber says something like “I thought you were mingling”

And of course she would’ve thought that:;

Andi is a ball of light that could make friends anywhere she goes

Amber didn’t expect her to be overwhelmed because she’s only ever seen the confident, bubbly side of Andi

But she immediately felt horrible about pushing her out of her comfort zone,

and freaked out when she thought that bex and bowie weren’t going to let Andi be friends with her anymore, ,,because Andi means that much to her

All I’m saying is; Amber has grown up so much and I’m so proud of my lesbian daughter

summary: i feel like since they leave so much development up to the texts and the texts might not always be around the show might not age...
question: i feel like since they leave so much development up to the texts and the texts might not always be around the show might not age as good as Id like it to? Because my friends that don't know about the texts will say they wish we could see things that we do get to see on the texts ,,, but idk what do you think
answer:
Oh the texts definitely will not age well at all. Not only do the majority of their audience have no idea the texts exist, but the concept surrounding the texts will become outdated as well because technology is constantly advancing. I usually hate when shows try to tie in social media, etc. because it never ages well - I just appreciate the texts because we know the writers are the ones doing it, not just some random Disney Channel intern, and I appreciate whatever extra context we can get lmao.

I think the show will age just fine for casual viewers though. Them not knowing about the texts doesn’t change much for their experience, as all of the episodes still make sense without the content in the texts. The show is really complex and has a hard time fitting into 20-minute time frames and such a strictly-determined number of episodes and rules surrounding the content of the show, so it sucks that they can’t always put everything in the show. Like not even just this recent Jonah/Andi conversation but also like… Andi and Cyrus talking about boys… Amber being worried that she got Andi grounded… I would like to see that stuff on screen more too, but I guess I’d rather have canon confirmations via the texts than not have it at all if that makes sense? Idk.
